<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1188634>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Identification of species of Conocephalus Thunberg, 1815 and Euxiphidion Bruner, 1915 of Mato Grosso do Sul (Brazil) studied here." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1188634/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1188638>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Tegmina and hind wings of Conocephalus Thunberg, 1815 (a–c) and Euxiphidion Bruner, 1915 (d–e) species. a Conocephalus goianus Piza, 1977; b Conocephalus saltator (Saussure, 1859); c Conocephalus versicolor (Redtenbacher, 1891); d Euxiphidion caizanum (Giglio-Tos, 1897) comb. nov.; e Euxiphidion veroni Chamorro-Rengifo sp. nov. Scale bars, 2.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1188638/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1188646>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Phallus of Conocephalus Thunberg, 1815 (a–c) and Euxiphidion Bruner, 1915 (d–e) species. Dorsal and ventral views. a Conocephalus goianus Piza, 1977; b Conocephalus saltator (Saussure, 1859); c Conocephalus versicolor (Redtenbacher, 1891); d Euxiphidion caizanum (Giglio-Tos, 1897) comb. nov.; e Euxiphidion veroni Chamorro-Rengifo sp. nov. Scale bars, 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1188646/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1188648>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Females subgenital plates of Conocephalus Thunberg, 1815 (a-c) and Euxiphidion Bruner, 1915 (d-e) species. Ventral view. a Conocephalus goianus Piza, 1977; b Conocephalus saltator (Saussure, 1859); c Conocephalus versicolor (Redtenbacher, 1891); d Euxiphidion caizanum (Giglio-Tos, 1897) comb. nov.; e Euxiphidion veroni Chamorro-Rengifo sp. nov. Scale bars, 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1188648/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1188654>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Songs of three species of Conocephalini. Upper oscillograms for each species represent 13-second fragments of continuous calling. (a–e) Conocephalus saltator (Saussure, 1859), (f–j) Conocephalus versicolor (Redtenbacher, 1891), (k–m) Euxiphidion veroni Chamorro-Rengifo sp. nov. a male in cage, 27.5ºC (specimen ZUFMSORT00532); b field recording, same time scale, 27.5 ºC (Pantanal, male photographed, but not collected); c last three syllables of first calling bout in b; d linear spectrogram of faint first hemisyllable; e the same of long second hemisyllable (from cage recording); f male calling in cage, 27.6ºC (ZUFMSORT00530); g first short isolated syllable from f; h last three syllables from first calling bout in f; i and j spectrograms of first and second hemisyllable; k male in plastic container, 26ºC (ZUFMSORT00686); l in finer scale; m spectrogram (1-kHz high-pass filtered, ultrasound portion missing)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1188654/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1188658>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Habitus of Euxiphidion caizanum (Giglio-Tos, 1897). (a–c) male: a lateral view; b dorsal view; c head in frontal view. d female, lateral view. Scale bars for a, b and d 5.0 mm; for c 1.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1188658/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1188660>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Live individuals of Euxiphidion Bruner, 1915 species. (a–b) Euxiphidion caizanum (Giglio-Tos, 1897), (c–d) Euxiphidion veroni Chamorro-Rengifo sp. nov. a male, dorso-lateral view; b female, dorso-lateral view; c male, dorso-lateral view; d female, dorso-lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1188660/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1188662>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Details of tegmina of Euxiphidion Bruner, 1915 species. (a-b) male left and right stridulatory files: a Euxiphidion caizanum (Giglio-Tos, 1897); b Euxiphidion veroni Chamorro-Rengifo sp. nov. (c-d) tegmina of females: c Exiphidion caizanum (Giglio-Tos) and d Euxiphidion veroni Chamorro-Rengifo sp. nov. Scale bars, 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1188662/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1188664>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Terminalia of Euxiphidion Bruner, 1915 species. Dorsal, lateral and ventral views. a Euxiphidion caizanum (Giglio-Tos, 1897); b Euxiphidion veroni Chamorro-Rengifo sp. nov. Scale bars, 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1188664/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1188666>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. Habitus of Euxiphidion veroni Chamorro-Rengifo sp. nov. (a–c) male: a lateral view; b dorsal view; c head in frontal view; d female, lateral view. Scale bars for a, b and d 5.0 mm; for c 1.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1188666/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1188670>
    dc:description "FIGURE 19. Diplotenes of Conocephalini. a Conocephalus goianus Piza, 1977, b Conocephalus saltator (Saussure, 1859), c Conocephalus versicolor (Redtenbacher, 1891), d Euxiphidion caizanum (Giglio-Tos, 1897) comb. nov., e Euxiphidion veroni Chamorro-Rengifo sp. nov.. a–c 16 autosomal bivalents and one sex univalent (16II + X); d and e 15 autosomal bivalents and one sex univalent (15II + X); a, d and e Giemsa staining; b and c telomeric fluorescent in situ hybridization. Scale bars, 5.0 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1188670/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1188672>
    dc:description "FIGURE 20. Mitotic metaphases of (a–c) Euxiphidion caizanum (Giglio-Tos, 1897) comb. nov. and (d–f) Euxiphidion veroni Chamorro-Rengifo sp. nov.. a and d spermatogonial, with 2n♂ = 31; b–c, e–f oogonial, with 2n♀= 32; a–b and d–e Giemsa staining; c and f telomeric fluorescent in situ hybridization. Scale bars, 5.0 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1188672/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

